<b>INFORMATION</b>
Name:		Viddle 
Info:		Video Search Web Application
Author:		hlavko (Mark Hlavac)
License:	Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 Unported License.

<b>HOW TO USE</b>

1. change set of crawling sites in ./conf/sites.dat where e.g.:
<URL> <REGEXP> <CRAWLER>

<URL> 		- URL where we will try to find our video content
<REGEXP>	- regexp anchor tags filter for concrete site
<CRAWLER>	- name of crawling method (sites have different methods for accessing video)

2. change mongodb access in ./conf/db.conf

3. start mining by:
python miner.py

notes: search index is created only at first launch

4. check logs in directory ./logs

5. start searching in index:

from viddle import search

query = search.Query()
query.search_term("hello")
